==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snot
<hw>Snot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>snot</ets>;
akin to D. <ets>snot</ets>, LG. <ets>snotte</ets>, Dan. <ets>snot</ets>,
and to E. <ets>snout</ets>. <ets>See</ets> <er>Snout</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Mucus secreted in, or discharged from, the nose.</def>
<mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mean, insignificant fellow.</def>
<mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snot
<hw>Snot</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To blow, wipe, or clear, as the
nose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snotter</ent>⟦br⟧
